comments.author: JFulfy

comments.text:
+JFulfy Agreed on Bulls, I'm just thinking about Rose. They won't go out 
without a fight, they have Hinrich, Butler, and Gasol : exceptional 
players. But, idk if exceptional will win them a championship. MJ held the 
Bulls throughout the series when they won their championship(s), maybe Rose 
will put the team on his back and try to ride through it, but yeah you're 
right about the Bulls, mentally they're not ready. I would say maybe next 
year. Maybe. The only reason why I feel the Hawks have a great shot at the 
championship because look at their record, they were absolutely one of the 
worst teams these past few years, especially with John Smith on the team. 
Smith left, look at them now. They're THE best team in the west. They came 
up lol. They're a threat to most of the teams in the playoffs. The Raptors 
have no chance. Nets? no chance. Pelicans? come on now. Look at the last 
series with the warriors, I expect it to be 4-0 for the warriors this time. 
Clippers? eh .. I don't know honestly. I wouldn't be surprised if they made 
it to the finals but man .. They're not clean either when it comes to 
"cheating" even though I feel they were robbed of a championship also if 
you look at the last playoffs with the thunder. That wasn't right. Rockets? 
Harden is one hell of a player and Howard defensively is arguably one of 
the best, but considering they'd have to go against the grizzlies and/or 
the Warriors, they'd lose. Terribly. I think the teams that have the best 
chances at winning are Spurs, Warriors, Atl, and Cavs. We gotta watch for 
the b.s. calls by the refs in all of the games, especially the cavs. I'll 
be upset if they win honestly. One of my fav players is Kyrie Irving, but 
the warriors deserve a ring. Curry deserves to be MVP.
